gomc circular-arc trajectory-planner regression test
=====================================================

test.sh / checkresult / arc.ngc / arc.ini / capture.hal / run-arc.py are the
automated regression test added for gomc: a full-circle G3 arc is run through the
gomc TP, the commanded X/Y joint path is captured every servo cycle by the
filestream cmod (capture.hal), and checkresult asserts every sample lies on the
commanded circle (centre (0,10), r=10) within 0.05 mm, and that the arc actually
swept the whole circle.

The other files in this directory (profile-run.sh, build-*.sh, machine_setup.py,
run_all_tests.py, octave/, *.tcl configs, nc_files/, ...) are the original
developer profiling / tuning harness (operf + octave plots + interactive prompts).
They are classic-LinuxCNC tooling (linuxcnc -r, TCL GUI) and are NOT part of the
automated suite; kept for reference only.
